# Personal Newsletter Config — Your Name

## Author
name: Your Name

## Sources
# Add only the sources you actually use. Unconfigured sources are skipped.
# If an MCP for a source isn't connected, it will be skipped gracefully.
sources:
  - confluence
  - google_drive
  - jira
  - github

## Publish target
# Where to publish the finished newsletter.
# Options: confluence | google_doc | markdown | notion
publish_target: confluence

## Confluence
# Required if confluence is in sources or publish_target is confluence.
confluence_space: your-space-key
parent_page_id: 123456789  # ID of your team's "Team Newsletters" page

## Google Doc
# Required if publish_target is google_doc.
# google_drive_folder_id: abc123  # optional: folder to put the doc in

## Markdown
# Required if publish_target is markdown.
# markdown_output_dir: ~/newsletters/

## GitHub
# Required if github is in sources.
orgs:
  - your-org
repos:
  - your-org/your-repo

## Manual sources (ask each run — can't be auto-searched)
# - LinkedIn: https://linkedin.com/in/you — ask "any LinkedIn posts this week?"
# - YouTube: ask "any videos published this week?"

## Custom questions
# custom_questions:
#   - "Any blog posts or external writing this week?"
#   - "Any conference talks or events to mention?"

## Notes
# Add any personal workflow preferences here.
# This file is updated automatically by Phase 5 after each run.
